---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Shahed Ali"
  description="Software engineer based in Bangalore. Here's who I am, what I'm working on, and how to reach me."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-12 opacity-0 animate-fade-up" style="animation-fill-mode: forwards;">
      <h1 class="text-[28px] sm:text-[34px] font-medium tracking-tight text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">
        Hey, I'm Shahed 👋
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[15px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
        Software engineer. Competitive programmer. Occasional over-thinker about systems. Based in Bangalore.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- About sections -->
    <div class="space-y-10 mb-16">

      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-medium text-ink-faint mb-4">The work</h2>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Right now I'm a Software Engineer at Uber (via Accenture), building <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Bliss-NXT</strong> — an internal support platform used by 30+ global teams. I own features end-to-end: from understanding the problem to shipping the fix. That means navigating Apollo GraphQL caching quirks just as much as writing clean TypeScript components that other engineers actually enjoy reading.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
          Before that, I spent 2.5 years at BeyondScale Technologies shipping things that actually mattered to real people — government portals that millions of citizens in Andhra Pradesh used every day, a fintech backend, US real estate data pipelines, a file management system. The stack changed constantly. The discipline didn't.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-medium text-ink-faint mb-4">How I think</h2>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">
          I compete on Codeforces, grind LeetCode, and genuinely enjoy the part where a problem seems impossible until it isn't. That mindset bleeds into everything I build — I'll sit with a hard bug longer than I should because I'd rather understand it than patch it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
          I believe good software is mostly about understanding the problem deeply, not picking the right framework. I've been wrong about this enough times in the right direction to be sure of it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-medium text-ink-faint mb-4">What I'm looking for</h2>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">
          A team where the work matters, ownership is real, and the bar is high enough that it forces you to grow. Frontend, full-stack, or anything in between — I care more about the problem than the title.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
          If you're building something serious and want someone who ships with care, here's my
          <a
            href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1eCQbX9U4Y32NQGJ7wE_bxV0MyNbx-jvz/view?usp=sharing"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-ink underline underline-offset-2 decoration-ink/30 hover:decoration-ink transition-all font-medium"
          >
            cover letter
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 opacity-60" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
          — a more honest version of what I'd say in a first call.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-medium text-ink-faint mb-4">Outside work</h2>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
          Working toward Candidate Master on Codeforces. Writing about DSA, system design, and the occasional thing I had to learn the hard way. Building this site as a slow, deliberate project — more garden than portfolio.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Cover letter CTA banner -->
    <div class="reveal mb-12">
      <a
        href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1eCQbX9U4Y32NQGJ7wE_bxV0MyNbx-jvz/view?usp=sharing"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="group flex items-center justify-between w-full px-5 py-4 rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface hover:border-ink-muted transition-all duration-200"
      >
        <div>
          <p class="text-[12px] uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-faint mb-1">Open to opportunities</p>
          <p class="text-[14px] text-ink font-medium">Read my cover letter →</p>
        </div>
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-ink-faint group-hover:text-ink group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6M15 3h6v6M10 14L21 3"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Contact form -->
    <div class="reveal border-t border-border pt-12">
      <h2 class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-medium text-ink-faint mb-2">Get in touch</h2>
      <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
        A role, a collab, something you read here that stuck — my inbox is genuinely open. I read every message.
      </p>

      <div id="form-success" class="hidden mb-6 p-4 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20">
        <p class="text-[13px] text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">✓ Message sent. I'll get back to you soon.</p>
      </div>

      <div id="form-error" class="hidden mb-6 p-4 rounded-lg bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/20">
        <p class="text-[13px] text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">Something went wrong. Email me directly at career@shahed.fyi</p>
      </div>

      <form id="contact-form" class="space-y-4">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <label class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-faint block mb-2">Name</label>
            <input
              type="text"
              id="name"
              required
              placeholder="Your name"
              class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 text-[13px] bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg text-ink placeholder:text-ink-faint focus:outline-none focus:border-ink-muted transition-colors"
            />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-faint block mb-2">Email</label>
            <input
              type="email"
              id="email"
              required
              placeholder="your@email.com"
              class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 text-[13px] bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg text-ink placeholder:text-ink-faint focus:outline-none focus:border-ink-muted transition-colors"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <label class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-faint block mb-2">Message</label>
          <textarea
            id="message"
            required
            rows="5"
            placeholder="What's on your mind..."
            class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 text-[13px] bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg text-ink placeholder:text-ink-faint focus:outline-none focus:border-ink-muted transition-colors resize-none"
          ></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center justify-end pt-2">
          <button
            type="submit"
            id="submit-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[13px] px-5 py-2.5 bg-ink text-surface rounded-lg hover:bg-ink/90 transition-colors font-medium disabled:opacity-50"
          >
            Send message
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>

<script define:vars={{
  EMAILJS_KEY: import.meta.env.PUBLIC_EMAILJS_KEY,
  EMAILJS_SERVICE: import.meta.env.PUBLIC_EMAILJS_SERVICE,
  EMAILJS_TEMPLATE: import.meta.env.PUBLIC_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE,
}}>
  const script = document.createElement('script');
  script.src = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@emailjs/browser@4/dist/email.min.js';
  script.onload = () => {
    emailjs.init(EMAILJS_KEY);
  };
  document.head.appendChild(script);

  const form = document.getElementById('contact-form');
  const btn = document.getElementById('submit-btn');
  const success = document.getElementById('form-success');
  const error = document.getElementById('form-error');

  form?.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();

    const name = document.getElementById('name').value;
    const email = document.getElementById('email').value;
    const message = document.getElementById('message').value;

    btn.disabled = true;
    btn.textContent = 'Sending...';

    try {
      await emailjs.send(
        EMAILJS_SERVICE,
        EMAILJS_TEMPLATE,
        { name, email, message }
      );

      success?.classList.remove('hidden');
      error?.classList.add('hidden');
      form.reset();
    } catch {
      error?.classList.remove('hidden');
      success?.classList.add('hidden');
    } finally {
      btn.disabled = false;
      btn.textContent = 'Send message';
    }
  });
</script>